'','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?p=10830',19,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10818,1,'2016-09-28 23:19:37','2016-09-28 23:19:37','','Envira Default Settings','','publish','closed','closed','','envira-default-gallery','','','2016-09-28 23:19:37','2016-09-28 23:19:37','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?post_type=envira&p=10818',0,'envira','',0),(10428,1,'2016-09-10 08:47:17','2016-09-10 15:47:17','','Envira Default Settings','','publish','closed','closed','','envira-default-gallery-2','','','2016-09-10 08:47:17','2016-09-10 15:47:17','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=envira&#038;p=10428',0,'envira','',0),(10429,1,'2016-09-10 08:56:54','2016-09-10 15:56:54','','Test gallery','','publish','closed','closed','','test-gallery','','','2016-09-10 08:56:54','2016-09-10 15:56:54','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=envira&#038;p=10429',0,'envira','',0),(10820,1,'2016-09-12 14:38:50','2016-09-12 21:38:50','','video gallery test','','publish','closed','closed','','video-gallery-test','','','2016-09-12 14:38:50','2016-09-12 21:38:50','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=envira&#038;p=10536',0,'envira','',0),(10821,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:47','2016-09-29 02:55:47','','events','','publish','closed','closed','','events-2','','','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/events-2/',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(9861,1,'2013-09-05 11:53:13','2013-09-05 19:53:13','<strong>Rev. angel Kyodo williams</strong> will be empowered as a fully authorized teacher in the Zen Buddhist tradition.\n\nmore info to come...','Dharma Transmission Ceremony','','publish','open','open','','dharma-transmission-ceremony','','','2013-09-05 11:53:13','2013-09-05 19:53:13','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=9861',0,'tribe_events','',0),(9917,1,'2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/akw-public_headshot23.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-9867\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/akw-public_headshot23-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"akw-public_headshot23.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nInformation is here about this event.','This is a new event','','publish','open','open','','this-is-a-new-event','','','2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=9917',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10201,1,'2015-10-31 14:14:26','2015-10-31 21:14:26','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-9984\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/iORUlJ79-ehmrlr4ytj4SH9pD2aN73wlj36r8tGGr_A-e1434159038485.jpg\" alt=\"Rev. angel Kyodo williams Sensei\" width=\"600\" height=\"250\" />\n\nAfter a summer and early fall full of travels as far as Istanbul, London and Amsterdam, angel Kyodo williams Sensei returns to her spiritual home, newDharma Community, to resume monthly public talks at the Center for Transformative Change.\n\nJoin us.','November Public Talk at Center for Transformative Change','angel Kyodo williams returns to her home at Center for Transformative Change to resume monthly public talks.','publish','open','closed','','public-talk-cxc-november','','','2015-10-31 14:14:26','2015-10-31 21:14:26','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10201',-1,'tribe_events','',0),(10208,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:22','2015-11-01 02:33:22','Held in the Washington, DC area, the day will offer wisdom teachings to liberate our own hearts, transform our communities and truly inspire an awakened society. Through meditation and discussion, participants will practice engaging personal and collective compassion in the path towards justice. Read more about the event and, if you\'ll be in DC Nov. 8, sign up <a href=\"http://bit.ly/1QgPQ8W\">here</a>.','Advancing Justice With Integrity','','publish','open','closed','','advancing-justice-with-integrity','','','2015-10-31 19:33:22','2015-11-01 02:33:22','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10208',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10209,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','Helping to kick off the opening of MNDFL, the hip new drop-in meditation studio in NYC, angel Kyodo Williams in conversation with special political guest  For the first time, angel, \"the most vocal and most intriguing  African-American Buddhist in America” (Library Journal) will be joined by a super special yet secret political guest for a dialogue around how meditation can spur us on to both love and justice. While angel is a meditation teacher who comes from the world of activism, our political guest is a long-standing meditator who can speak to how it helps him in government. You\'ve heard how meditation can lower stress, increase memory, and more, but learn how it can help you love more fully and bring more justice to today\'s world.\n\n\n','Love and Justice at MNDFL','angel will be joined by a surprise political guest for a dialogue around how meditation can spur us on to both love and justice. While angel is a meditation teacher who comes from the world of activism, our political guest is a long-standing meditator who can speak to how it helps him in government.','publish','open','closed','','love-and-justice-at-mndfl','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10209',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10210,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','angel Kyodo williams talks about the impact of unconscious bias on leadership and how mindfuless can help. There is an alternative to just leading from the top down.It\'s leading from the inside out.\n\nThat’s what mindful leadership is all about. It’s about recognizing that your leadership is in service to others. It’s about creating the space in your life to cultivate self-awareness and compassion, and leading with authenticity in a way that inspires others. Doing this, we can transform our own lives, our organizations, our communities – and the world.','Mindful Leadership Summit','','publish','open','closed','','mindful-leadership-summit','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10210',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10211,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','angel joins in alongside over 30 of the world’s leading experts on meditation and mindfulness for a series of online interviews, practice sessions and presentations taking place for FREE from October 1 – 31, 2015.','The Mindfulness Summit','','publish','open','closed','','the-mindfulness-summit','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10211',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10212,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','Hosted by Shambhala Mountain Center, this is the 2nd Annual online event exploring Mindfulness and Yoga in our Health, Relationships and Work as a Path to Personal and Societal Transformation. 30 Exclusive Video Dialogues and Presentations with Top Thought Leaders, Wisdom Holders, and Social Visionaries. During the series, angel enjoys a conversation with Dr. James Doty, a neurosurgeon that founded CCARE, Center for Compassion and Altruism Research and Education at Stanford. She is also interviewed by the insightful Shambhala Shastri Trinley Busby.','Awake In the World','','publish','open','closed','','awake-in-the-world','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10212',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10213,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','Rev. angel Kyodo williams and Ximena Savitch give the opening blessings at the site of the Fight for 15 campaign\'s strike day. Yogis and meditators from all over New York City are standing with striking low-wage workers to support a raise to the minimum wage. Our practice challenges us to create unity and wellbeing not just within ourselves, but to play a role in creating the conditions of wellbeing for all people. We\'ll meet as a group at 5:30 AM on Tuesday, Nov 10th at the Starbucks at 348 Fulton in Brooklyn, march alongside 1,000 low wage workers, and then grab a healthy breakfast and head back to Brooklyn Yoga Project for a shared meditation practice and story share with workers until 9 AM. We hope you\'ll join us to put our practice into <a href=\"http://bit.ly/NovFF15\">action</a>.','Fight for 15 Strike Day w/ CTZNWELL','','publish','open','closed','','fight-for-15-strike-day-w-ctznwell','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10213',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10214,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','Lecture at Department of Philosophy and Religious Studies at St. Francis College. Open to students only.','St. Francis College Lecture','','publish','open','closed','','st-francis-college-lecture','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10214',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10215,1,'2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','tba','Brooklyn Zen Center','','publish','open','closed','','brooklyn-zen-center','','','2015-10-31 19:33:23','2015-11-01 02:33:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10215',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10253,1,'2015-11-19 21:31:33','0000-00-00 00:00:00','test','test','','draft','open','closed','','','','','2015-11-19 21:31:33','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10253',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10365,1,'2016-09-06 11:30:28','2016-09-06 18:30:28','<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/akw-blue_wide.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-10659 alignleft\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/akw-blue_wide-300x125.jpg\" alt=\"akw-blue_wide\" width=\"525\" height=\"219\" /></a>\n<blockquote><em>An in-the-know informal talk for current residents and visitors at the near-idyllic Green Gulch Zen Center and Farm. The topic, leaning into her October 15 TEDx talk, will be on how letting go of ideas of love might be just the thing you need. Now you know.</em></blockquote>','Green Gulch Zen Center &#038; Farm','','publish','open','closed','','green-gulch-farms','','','2016-09-06 11:30:28','2016-09-06 18:30:28','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10365',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10367,1,'2016-09-06 11:34:06','2016-09-06 18:34:06','<span id=\"gmail-docs-internal-guid-312e1154-3581-3b92-602f-c34f3aa6b3d7\">Kyodo Sensei (as she is  known in Zen circles) returns to her second home  at Brooklyn Zen Center where she is a visiting teacher. Her Saturday morning dharma talks here are full bodied, deep dives into dharma that matters today. \"Seeing Suffering: Four Truths to Save Your Life\" is a remix of the classic first teaching of the historic Buddha. A perfect intro for beginners new and old.</span>','Seeing Suffering: Four Truths to Save Your Life','','publish','open','closed','','seeing-suffering-four-truths-save-your-life','','','2016-09-06 11:34:06','2016-09-06 18:34:06','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10367',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10368,1,'2016-09-06 11:37:57','2016-09-06 11:37:57','<div class=\"__pbConvBody\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_embodied.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-10765 size-medium\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_embodied-227x300.jpg\" alt=\"angel Kyodo williams, Sensei\" width=\"227\" height=\"300\" /></a>This evening follows up on the Saturday, October 8th talk, \"Seeing Suffering: Four Truths to Save Your Life,\" taking it beyond concept and landing it in the direct experience of embodied practice.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Rev angel will create space for engaging conversation and practice that disrupts limiting storylines and experiential exercises that help us manifest the liberating potential of the dharma through uncompromising practice.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Hands-on instruction will be offered to guide you to develop a deeper relationship with the suffering you inevitably carry in your own being, physically, psychologically, emotionally and socially. You\'ll discover that you can access joy in the midst of suffering rather than remain committed to the delusion of \"when things are different than they are.\"</p>\nThis evening is a rare opportunity to experience what Rev. angel calls Third Way Training: bridging training of the heart-mind with training of the body-mind. It\'s a perfect introduction to the powerful Free Your Body: Oppression In the Soma retreat she co-facilitates later this fall.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Seeing Suffering: Embodied Practice','This evening follows up on the Saturday, October 8th talk, \"Seeing Suffering: Four Truths to Save Your Life,\" taking it beyond concept and landing it in the direct experience of embodied practice.','publish','open','closed','','seeing-suffering-embodied','','','2016-10-11 02:17:43','2016-10-11 02:17:43','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10368',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10369,1,'2016-09-06 11:50:51','2016-09-06 18:50:51','\"It\'s Not About Love After All\" turns everything we thought inside out and is the talk angel will give for the Practice Change theme of this TEDx to be held in the very heart of New York City. The talk is based on a chapter of the same name in her book <a href=\"http://radicaldharma.org\" target=\"_blank\">Radical Dharma: Talking Race, Love &amp; Liberation</a>. Rev. angel joins Sharon Salzberg, Eileen Fisher and other notables. Most importantly, a thick group of friends and compañer@s on the path of change will be there: Aqeela Sherrills, Carla Goldstein, Claudia Horwitz, Kerri Kelly and Marisela Gomez will make it a Deep Change Fest.\r\n\r\nTickets will sell out fast. Get yours today.','TEDx Washington Square','\"It\'s Not About Love After All\" turns everything we thought inside out and is the talk angel will give for the Practice Change theme of this TEDx to be held in the very heart of New York City. The talk is based on a chapter of the same name in her book Radical Dharma: Talking Race, Love & Liberation. ','publish','open','closed','','tedx-washington-square','','','2016-10-11 02:15:07','2016-10-11 02:15:07','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10369',-1,'tribe_events','',0),(10371,1,'2016-09-06 11:53:07','2016-09-06 11:53:07','<em><strong>Zen and the Art of Love</strong></em> is the topic of the moment as angel returns to MNDFL (yup, pronounced \"mindful\") the very groovy but also very practical, accessible meditation lounge also located in the heart of NYC\'s village. Skeptical? If you haven\'t read about it, there is praise galore to be found.','Zen and the Art of Love - MNDFL','','publish','open','closed','','zen-and-art-of-love-mndfl','','','2016-10-11 02:17:51','2016-10-11 02:17:51','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10371',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10372,1,'2016-09-06 11:57:03','2016-09-06 18:57:03','<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-10442 alignleft\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma-223x300.jpg\" alt=\"akw_dharma\" width=\"223\" height=\"300\" /></a>Durham is a city in which many polarized perspectives meet. Here, a Friday evening public talk on Radical Dharma is followed by a weekend workshop on Embodied Race &amp; Power Awareness, Rev. angel\'s signature training in which race&amp;power meets the dharma and lands in the body. <em>\"Through practices of centering, contextualization, conversation and community, we prepare ourselves to recognize and disrupt limiting habit-patterns as a gateway to love and liberation—of self and society.</em>\"\n\n<strong>Read the Event here</strong>: http://durham.shambhala.org/program-details/?id=266702','Shambhala Durham: Embodied Race &amp; Power Awareness','','publish','open','closed','','embrace-durham-shambhala','','','2016-09-06 11:57:03','2016-09-06 18:57:03','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10372',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10374,1,'2016-09-06 11:59:26','2016-09-06 18:59:26','<img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_headshot-244x300.jpg\" alt=\"akw_headshot\" />Durham is a city in which many polarized perspectives meet. Here, a Friday evening public talk on Radical Dharma is followed by a weekend workshop on Embodied Race &amp; Power Awareness, Rev. angel\'s signature training in which race&amp;power meets the dharma and lands in the body. \"Through practices of centering, contextualization, conversation and community, we prepare ourselves to recognize and disrupt limiting habit-patterns as a gateway to love and liberation—of self and society.\"\n\n<strong>Read the event here</strong>: <a href=\"http://durham.shambhala.org/program-details/?id=276708\">http://durham.shambhala.org/program-details/?id=276708</a>','Shambhala Durham Radical Dharma Public Talk','','publish','open','closed','','radical-dharma-durham-shambhala','','','2016-09-06 11:59:26','2016-09-06 18:59:26','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10374',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10376,1,'2016-09-06 12:08:26','2016-09-06 19:08:26','Mindful leadership is about leading from the inside, out and recognizing that your leadership is in service to others. It’s about creating the space in your life to cultivate self-awareness and compassion, and leading with authenticity in a way that inspires others. Doing this, we can transform our own lives, our organizations, our communities – and the world. Mindful Leadership Summit features 25+ presenters including Dr. Dan Siegel, Emma Seppala, Otto Scharmer, Marc Lesser, and our very own Rev. angel Kyodo williams.\n\nwhat they say:\nOrganizations around the world are waking up to awareness, authenticity and compassion as important qualities in leadership. The Mindful Leadership Summit, which has become the largest mindful leadership event in the world, brings together leaders from across the country to foster mindfulness and compassion in the workplace.\n\nThe Mindful Leadership Summit features a renowned group of 25+ presenters, including Dr. Dan Siegel, Emma Seppala, Otto Scharmer, Marc Lesser, Rose Pavlov, Janice Marturano, Drew Hansen, and Rasmus Hougaard. In the last two years, our events have brought together over 1,000 leaders. This two-day event will include group workshops, keynote speakers, social events, and somatic exercises.\n\n-Learn practical tools and best practices\n-Share success stories and challenges\n-Develop your leadership skills\n-Build community with people seeking a more meaningful and effective kind of leadership\n\nThe Summit brings together leaders from all organizational levels and various backgrounds, including business, non-profit, education, health &amp; wellness, and government. This is a unique opportunity to connect with people who share the desire for a more meaningful and effective kind of leadership.\n\nJoin us at this significant moment in the evolution of leadership - November 4-5, 2016 at the Crystal Gateway Marriott, DC Metro Area.\n','Mindful Leadership Summit','','publish','open','closed','','mindful-leadership-summit-2','','','2016-09-06 12:08:26','2016-09-06 19:08:26','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10376',0,'tribe_events','',0),(9862,1,'2013-09-05 11:53:13','2013-09-05 19:53:13','','The Oaks','','publish','open','open','','the-oaks','','','2013-09-05 11:53:13','2013-09-05 19:53:13','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/the-oaks/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(9918,1,'2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','','newDharma Community','','publish','open','open','','newdharma-community','','','2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/organizer/newdharma-community/',0,'tribe_organizer','',0),(9919,1,'2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','','Center for Transformative Change','','publish','open','open','','center-for-transformative-change','','','2015-05-24 15:11:12','2015-05-24 23:11:12','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/center-for-transformative-change/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10204,1,'2015-10-31 18:48:15','2015-11-01 01:48:15','','Shambhala Mountain Center','','publish','closed','closed','','shambhala-mountain-center','','','2015-10-31 18:48:15','2015-11-01 01:48:15','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_organizer&#038;p=10204',0,'tribe_organizer','',0),(10205,1,'2015-10-31 18:49:43','2015-11-01 01:49:43','See website for details','Online','','publish','closed','closed','','online','','','2015-10-31 18:49:43','2015-11-01 01:49:43','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_venue&#038;p=10205',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10206,1,'2015-10-31 19:13:23','2015-11-01 02:13:23','','Brooklyn Zen Center','','publish','closed','closed','','brooklyn-zen-center','','','2015-10-31 19:13:23','2015-11-01 02:13:23','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_venue&#038;p=10206',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10207,1,'2015-10-31 19:14:14','2015-11-01 02:14:14','','Brooklyn Zen Center','','publish','closed','closed','','brooklyn-zen-center','','','2015-10-31 19:14:14','2015-11-01 02:14:14','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_organizer&#038;p=10207',0,'tribe_organizer','',0),(10217,1,'2015-11-02 10:43:33','2015-11-02 18:43:33','','MNDFL','','publish','closed','closed','','mndfl','','','2015-11-02 10:43:33','2015-11-02 18:43:33','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/mndfl/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10230,1,'2015-11-03 17:07:14','2015-11-04 01:07:14','','THEARC','','publish','closed','closed','','thearc','','','2015-11-03 17:07:14','2015-11-04 01:07:14','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_venue&#038;p=10230',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10231,1,'2015-11-04 12:52:55','2015-11-04 20:52:55','','THEARC','','publish','closed','closed','','thearc-2','','','2015-11-04 12:52:55','2015-11-04 20:52:55','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/thearc-2/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10366,1,'2016-09-06 11:30:29','2016-09-06 18:30:29','','Green Gulch Zen Center','','publish','closed','closed','','green-gulch-zen-center','','','2016-09-06 11:30:29','2016-09-06 18:30:29','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/green-gulch-zen-center/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10370,1,'2016-09-06 11:50:51','2016-09-06 18:50:51','','Tishman Auditorium at New York University','','publish','closed','closed','','tishman-auditorium-at-new-york-university','','','2016-09-06 11:50:51','2016-09-06 18:50:51','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/tishman-auditorium-at-new-york-university/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10379,1,'2016-09-06 12:16:38','2016-09-06 19:16:38','Radical Dharma returns home to ATL. An evening public talk with this warm community is followed by a daylong training at the historic MLK Center on what Talking Race, Love &amp; Liberation really means rooted in community. A not-to-be-missed launch of Rev. angel\'s newest training based on material from the critically acclaimed book.','Shambhala Atlanta: Radical Dharma training','','publish','open','closed','','radical-dharma-atlanta-shambhala','','','2016-09-06 12:16:38','2016-09-06 19:16:38','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10379',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10382,1,'2016-09-06 12:48:18','2016-09-06 19:48:18','','Rusia Mohuiddin &amp; angel Kyodo williams','','publish','closed','closed','','rusia-mohuiddin-angel-kyodo-williams','','','2016-09-06 12:48:18','2016-09-06 19:48:18','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/organizer/rusia-mohuiddin-angel-kyodo-williams/',0,'tribe_organizer','',0),(10384,1,'2016-09-06 13:05:59','2016-09-06 20:05:59','<strong>Can you say transformation?</strong>\n\nNow...can you be it? This weeklong retreat fulfills a dream to design a gathering in which every aspect of the conditions required for transformation is considered. Environment and timing. Face-to-face ZenChange sessions for precise individual assessment and follow-up. Healing through modalities of body, breath and sound. Practices that dislodge limiting beliefs embedded in our stories, language, body and movements.\n\nGuest Sound Healer <a href=\"http://vibrationofgrace.com\" target=\"_blank\">gina Breedlove </a>will be offering two full group Sound Healing circles and opportunities for one-on-one sessions with her will be available.\n\n<em>This retreat is by application &amp; interview only.</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6941.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-10414 size-large\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6941-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"img_6941\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6882.jpg\"> </a><a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6841.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10416\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6841-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"img_6841\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6882.jpg\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10415\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/IMG_6882-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"img_6882\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /> </a>\n\n<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huiho-pool.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-10401 size-full\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huiho-pool.jpg\" alt=\"huiho-pool\" width=\"400\" height=\"290\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huiho-room.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10399\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huiho-room-218x300.jpg\" alt=\"huiho-room\" width=\"218\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huio-sunset.jpg\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10400\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/huio-sunset-218x300.jpg\" alt=\"huio-sunset\" width=\"218\" height=\"300\" /></a>','be.transformation: place. spirit. sound.','','publish','open','closed','','be-transformation-retreat','','','2016-09-06 13:05:59','2016-09-06 20:05:59','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10384',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10505,1,'2016-09-11 20:04:06','2016-09-12 03:04:06','<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/0.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-10537 alignleft\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/0-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"What is Transformative Change?\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Are you a director, CEO or senior staff member needing to lose the baggage that you know is holding you back? </em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">This intensive format of the powerful #FreeYourBody Retreat is specially crafted for folks working their A-game that need their B-behavior behind them. Hands down the most powerful and grounded transformation you\'ll experience in this short a duration. Stuff that works and stuff that sticks when you can\'t afford to wander through the weeds of dysfunction any longer. Registration is highly selective, so bring your A-game starting now.</p>','#FreeYourBody Intensive','','publish','open','closed','','freeyourbody-intensive','','','2016-09-11 20:04:06','2016-09-12 03:04:06','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/?post_type=tribe_events&#038;p=10505',0,'tribe_events','',0),(10507,1,'2016-09-11 20:04:06','2016-09-12 03:04:06','','Millerton NY','','inherit','closed','closed','','millerton-ny','','','2016-09-11 20:04:06','2016-09-12 03:04:06','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/millerton-ny/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10938,1,'2016-10-19 21:24:41','2016-10-19 21:24:41','','Gallery Post Test','','publish','closed','closed','','gallery-post-test','','','2016-10-19 21:30:26','2016-10-19 21:30:26','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?post_type=envira&#038;p=10938',0,'envira','',0),(10939,1,'2016-10-19 21:25:44','2016-10-19 21:25:44','[envira-gallery id=\"10938\"]','Photo Gallery Test','','publish','closed','closed','','photo-gallery-test','','','2016-10-19 21:25:44','2016-10-19 21:25:44','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?post_type=gallery&#038;p=10939',0,'gallery','',0),(10940,1,'2016-10-19 21:27:09','2016-10-19 21:27:09','[envira-gallery id=\"10938\"]','Image Gallery','Photos from angel\'s trips abroad (replace this txt)','publish','open','open','','gallery','','','2016-10-23 17:59:05','2016-10-23 17:59:05','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?p=10940',0,'post','',0),(10941,1,'2016-10-19 21:27:09','2016-10-19 21:27:09','[envira-gallery id=\"10938\"]','Gallery Test','','inherit','closed','closed','','10940-revision-v1','','','2016-10-19 21:27:09','2016-10-19 21:27:09','',10940,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/19/10940-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10942,1,'2016-10-19 21:31:07','2016-10-19 21:31:07','[envira-gallery id=\"10938\"]','Image Gallery Test','','inherit','closed','closed','','10940-revision-v1','','','2016-10-19 21:31:07','2016-10-19 21:31:07','',10940,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/19/10940-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10943,1,'2016-10-19 21:31:36','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Video Gallery Test','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-10-19 21:31:36','2016-10-19 21:31:36','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?post_type=envira&#038;p=10943',0,'envira','',0),(10944,1,'2016-10-19 23:11:47','2016-10-19 23:11:47','<h3 style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"wp-image-10449 alignleft\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/williams_angel_kyodo_web_1.jpg\" alt=\"williams_angel_kyodo_web_1\" width=\"278\" height=\"417\" />An Interview With angel Kyodo williams</h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify\">In this interview, Zen teacher, activist, and author of Being Black: Zen and the Art of Living with Fearlessness and Grace <a href=\"http://www.eomega.org/workshops/teachers/angel-kyodo-williams-0\" target=\"_blank\">angel Kyodo williams</a> talks with Omega about the path from inner work to social change.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Omega: You’ve said, “The heart that hurts is the very same heart that heals.” How do we build a bridge from personal to collective healing, and apply inner gentleness to systems and structures that urgently need to alter?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>angel</em>: I think it’s incumbent upon us waving our flags about inner work during such a pressing experience of social ills and destabilization to respond—at least as best we can.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">One main challenge of approaching transformation in society through inner work is that people think it means focusing on others: “If I feel this way about that person....” Then we’re up against a struggle to navigate all the people not in our tribe or chosen collective. Our society is broken and we are challenged with a systematic structure that has kept us divided. We mistakenly think the way to get beyond it is to have compassion for other people in a sort of bland way and it’ll all get better, but that hasn’t been working.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">My sense of the path from inner work to social change is for each of us to be much more intimate with our own self, and the brokenness and suffering that we ourselves experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">That’s not to be mistaken with a fixation on me, me, me, but rather a true, intimate relationship (which is Buddhism’s stamp) with our own suffering. When we touch suffering deeply, it becomes very apparent that we would not want anyone to experience the suffering. So that we’re not saying, “I know the suffering of my broken heartedness. I know the suffering of being witness to prejudice and people being marginalized and mistreated and denied opportunity. But I can’t touch them because it’s too hard.” It takes courage and practice and a developed capacity to really touch the heart of our own suffering because it feels uncomfortable. We’re not taught to tolerate discomfort—but quite the opposite—to get away from discomfort as quickly as possible and paper it over with television and Facebook and all manner of things.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">So touching inner work to social transformation is about willingness and touching the heart of our own suffering, out of which arises an organic understanding that we would not want anyone else to experience such suffering and, therefore, we wish for their well-being. The deeper we go into our suffering the more fervent the wish for the well-being of others. We act. We act because our inaction is felt as a participation in that suffering.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Omega</em>: Communities around the country are struggling to respond to violence with grace. How do you reach for curiosity as a tool to access courage and vulnerability in difficult moments?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>angel</em>: I access curiosity by being curious about my own feelings. When I enter a situation and notice that I’m experiencing discomfort or I’m disassociated or cut off from my feelings, I become exquisitely curious about that. Where is that feeling of disconnect arising from? What could it be? I follow it with the curiosity of a child. They don’t just run in and throw the closet open but follow the breadcrumbs of this tiny piece of experience: this way that my stomach feels clenched; this way that I notice the room got darker and more narrow; this way that I notice that dark face in front of me brings a little bit of quickness to my breath. What is it about this dark face that should bring a quickness to my breath? What is actually there?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">You’re following breadcrumbs, not saying, “Hey, you’re some person I’m feeling some anxiety and fear about. I don\'t know where it comes from, but let me come and hug you.” Rather, what is this experience of contraction or disconnect with the human being in front of me?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If I really feel out of sorts, I might get in touch with the grief that generally attends our loss of contact. If we’re feeling disconnected, right behind it—if we can stay planted right where we are instead of running away from the feeling and the space—we’ll notice that hidden behind that experience is a very subtle sense of grief. Because we’re fundamentally oriented to be connected to one another, so we can’t experience anything but grief when we are disconnected. Our anger and reactivity, our running away and taking flight—all of that is a result of being mortified that we’re having an inappropriate experience of our humanity. We are experiencing loss—a moment of disconnect from our own humanity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If we are not trained, we may react by lashing out. Just like small children react to being frightened by screaming, crying, hiding in a corner, or running away. It is maturity that enables us to stay put and notice the sensations and be curious about where they’re coming from and follow the breadcrumbs back to the connection.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Omega</em>: People often walk a self-conscious line between belonging in, or even “representing,” a larger community and expressing their individual uniqueness. Diversity is a strength, but many movements, and individuals, experience internal fracturing. How do we practice holism as individuals and collectively?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>angel</em>: Problems arise when someone gets the idea they have the right understanding or view on how the whole should express itself and doesn\'t allow for the unique permutations that are the gift of diversity. We become controlling about how people ought to show up or do things.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">On the other hand we can become obsessed with expressing our uniqueness precisely because we don’t feel like we belong. We can get overly engaged with the need to express ourselves. That’s a direct response to not feeling seen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">These two things are connected. When the whole doesn’t try to make everyone conform but realizes a plethora of diverse expressions of the whole as valid, then individuals can soften because they truly belong and they don’t have to assert an obsession around identity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">All we’re grappling with fundamentally is our sense of overwhelming separation. We’re just kicking and screaming and thrashing because we want to belong. And we need that, as a socially organized primate, right? We need to belong.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">This society was built on division right from the beginning—division was not only fostered, it was constructed, then fostered, then institutionalized, and then concretized in law, in all ways.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Imagine a family unit—what would it be like for children to feel so cut off from what is now their family? To be told in so many ways, you are not really a part of this family. You don’t really belong here. We didn’t really want you. And if you are going to be here, the only way you can be here is at a great disadvantage, so that your lack of belonging is assured.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">At the heart of what ails so much of marginalized communities, is how much they want to belong, which we never really say, and we don’t say that what ails so many white, hetero, cis-gendered men is their wanting to belong, and not. What if we could say, “Oh, here’s what’s happening: We are brokenhearted because we feel forced in this society to cut ourselves off from our humanity in order to maintain this outdated, always demeaning, dehumanizing structure that was designed to afford privileges and economic advantage to a few on the backs of many”? We all are graded in that way, and in pain as a result.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If we can’t belong, then we want to be special. We want to be a celebrity. We all have our own personal media platforms. How crazy is this? I’ve got four of them myself. It’s like The angel Show and I\'m always directing and producing and writing and projecting out this angel critter. We just really want to belong and be seen. The social media and technological moment that we find ourselves in is such a very strong expression of exactly what is going on with us. We want to be heard. We want to matter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>Read the interview here:</strong> https://www.eomega.org/article/social-justice-buddhism</p>','Social Justice & Buddhism','','inherit','closed','closed','','10455-revision-v1','','','2016-10-19 23:11:47','2016-10-19 23:11:47','',10455,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/19/10455-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10373,1,'2016-09-06 11:57:03','2016-09-06 18:57:03','','Durham Shambhala','','publish','closed','closed','','durham-shambhala','','','2016-09-06 11:57:03','2016-09-06 18:57:03','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/durham-shambhala/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10375,1,'2016-09-06 11:59:26','2016-09-06 18:59:26','','Durham Shambhala','','publish','closed','closed','','durham-shambhala-2','','','2016-09-06 11:59:26','2016-09-06 18:59:26','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/durham-shambhala-2/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10377,1,'2016-09-06 12:08:26','2016-09-06 19:08:26','','Crystal Gateway Marriott','','publish','closed','closed','','crystal-gateway-marriott','','','2016-09-06 12:08:26','2016-09-06 19:08:26','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/crystal-gateway-marriott/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10380,1,'2016-09-06 12:16:38','2016-09-06 19:16:38','','Atlanta Shambhala','','publish','closed','closed','','atlanta-shambhala','','','2016-09-06 12:16:38','2016-09-06 19:16:38','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/atlanta-shambhala/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10383,1,'2016-09-06 12:48:19','2016-09-06 19:48:19','','The Watershed Center','','publish','closed','closed','','the-watershed-center','','','2016-09-06 12:48:19','2016-09-06 19:48:19','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/the-watershed-center/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10385,1,'2016-09-06 13:05:59','2016-09-06 20:05:59','','Hui Ho&#039;olana','','publish','closed','closed','','hui-hoolana','','','2016-09-06 13:05:59','2016-09-06 20:05:59','',0,'http://angelkyodowilliams.com/venue/hui-hoolana/',0,'tribe_venue','',0),(10822,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:52','2016-09-29 02:55:52','is regarded as a gifted communicator of the essence of Dharma, the universal truth that leads to freedom. Named “the most intriguing African-American Buddhist in America” by Library Journal, Kyodoshi, as she is affectionately called, is known for her ability to make profound wisdom teaching relevant to everyday life.   angel Kyodo is the “Mahamitra” or great spiritual friend of the New Dharma Community, which has its physical home in Berkeley,CA with members in NY, MA and as far away as Lebanon. she is a maverick within her root tradition of zen buddhism, holding an interest in articulating relevant expressions of the essence of zen. Her dharma name, Kyodo, means “way of teaching.” At her priest ordination ceremony, the suffix “-ji” meaning compassion, was added by her preceptor, Paco Genkoji Lugoviña, so that her full dharma name is something akin to: Way of Teaching Compassion. while she is humbled and sometimes chagrined by the enormity of practicing this name, she is fully committed to doing just that by any means necessary: in an unflinching, authentic way, not bound by social convention, political correctness, the desire to appeal to student’s favor or for financial gain.     Kyodoshi-mitra lives as a…','about','','publish','closed','closed','','about-2','','','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/about-2/',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10823,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:52','2016-09-29 02:55:52',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','10823','','','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/10823/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10824,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:52','2016-09-29 02:55:52',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','10824','','','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/10824/',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10829,1,'2016-09-29 03:05:20','2016-09-29 03:05:20','','audio','','publish','closed','closed','','audio','','','2016-10-25 06:31:08','2016-10-25 06:31:08','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/?p=10829',17,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10827,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:52','2016-09-29 02:55:52',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','10827','','','2016-09-29 02:58:43','2016-09-29 02:58:43','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/10827/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10828,1,'2016-09-29 02:55:52','2016-09-29 02:55:52','','contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-4','','','2016-09-29 02:58:43','2016-09-29 02:58:43','',0,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/09/29/contact-4/',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(10837,1,'2016-10-10 02:50:54','2016-10-10 02:50:54','<h3>???</h3>','Main','','inherit','closed','closed','','105-revision-v1','','','2016-10-10 02:50:54','2016-10-10 02:50:54','',105,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/10/105-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10838,1,'2016-10-10 03:08:33','2016-10-10 03:08:33','<h3>???</h3>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','105-revision-v1','','','2016-10-10 03:08:33','2016-10-10 03:08:33','',105,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/10/105-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10839,1,'2016-10-10 04:37:50','2016-10-10 04:37:50','<a href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Angel1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Angel1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"449\" height=\"307\" /></a>\r\n\r\nCalled \"the most intriguing African-American Buddhist\" by <em>Library Journal</em>, Rev. angel Kyodo williams Sensei, is an author, maverick spiritual teacher, master trainer and founder of Center for Transformative Change. She has been bridging the worlds of personal transformation and justice since the publication of her critically-acclaimed book, <em>Being Black: Zen and the Art of Living With Fearlessness and Grace</em>. Her book was hailed as “an act of love” by Pulitzer Prize winner Alice Walker and “a classic” by Buddhist teacher Jack Kornfield. Her new book, <em><a href=\"http://radicaldharma.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Radical Dharma</a></em>, explores racial injustice as a barrier to collective awakening.\r\n\r\nOrdained as a Zen priest, she is a <em>Sensei</em>, the second black woman recognized as a teacher in her lineage. She is a social visionary that applies wisdom teachings and practice to social issues. She sees Transformative Social Change as America’s next great movement.  She is an early shaper and leading voice in that work and coined the name for the field. In recognition of her work, Rev. angel received the first Creating Enlightened Society Award from Sakyong Mipham Rinpoche, the leader of the international Shambhala Community.\r\n\r\nFor over 15 years, she has deeply invested her time and energy to putting into practice her unwavering belief that the key to transforming society is transforming our inner lives. She has developed comprehensive systems for illuminating both practical personal change and the profoundly liberating potential of mindfulness, yoga, and somatic practices coupled with wisdom teachings. Calling for a paradigm shift that “changes the way change is done,” angel envisions the building of a presence-centered social justice movement as the foundation for personal freedom, a just society and the healing of divisions of race, class, faith and politic.\r\n\r\nBoth fierce and grounded, she is known for her unflinching willingness to both sit with and speak uncomfortable truths with love. Her work has been widely covered by such publications as <em>New York Times</em>, <em>Boston Globe</em>, <em>Ms.</em>, Essence, <em>Buddhadharma</em>, <em>Village Voice</em>, and on the <em>Oxygen Channel</em>. angel notes, \"Love and justice are not two. Without inner change, there can be no outer change. Without collective change, no change matters.\" Whether in writing, teaching or speaking, her voice is unique.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','bio','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-revision-v1','','','2016-10-10 04:37:50','2016-10-10 04:37:50','',18,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/10/18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10840,1,'2016-10-13 00:56:18','2016-10-13 00:56:18','<a class=\"post-top-image\" href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-10442 size-medium\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma-223x300.jpg\" alt=\"akw_dharma\" width=\"223\" height=\"300\" /></a><em> By Garrison Institute</em>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As part of our “Garrison Talks at the JCC” event series, teachers and authors Sharon Salzberg and Rev. angel Kyodo williams recently discussed ways to bridge spiritual practice and social activism. Some of the key questions explored:</p>\n\n<ul>\n 	<li>Does spiritual practice require that we love everyone?</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Does being happy mean that we avoid conflict?</li>\n 	<li>How can we speak differently about spiritual practice and social justice so that we honor both where we are now and where we want to go?</li>\n</ul>\n\n','Bridging Spirituality and Activism','Does spiritual practice require that we love everyone?\nDoes being happy mean that we avoid conflict?\nHow can we speak differently about spiritual practice and social justice so that we honor both where we are now and where we want to go?\n\nAs part of our “Garrison Talks at the JCC” event series, teachers and authors Sharon Salzberg and Rev. angel Kyodo williams recently discussed ways to bridge spiritual practice and social activism.','inherit','closed','closed','','10642-autosave-v1','','','2016-10-13 00:56:18','2016-10-13 00:56:18','',10642,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/10/10642-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10841,1,'2016-10-10 16:20:29','2016-10-10 16:20:29','<a class=\"post-top-image\" href=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-10442 size-medium\" src=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/aKw_dharma-223x300.jpg\" alt=\"akw_dharma\" width=\"223\" height=\"300\" /></a><em> By Garrison Institute</em>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As part of our “Garrison Talks at the JCC” event series, teachers and authors Sharon Salzberg and Rev. angel Kyodo williams recently discussed ways to bridge spiritual practice and social activism. Some of the key questions explored:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Does spiritual practice require that we love everyone?</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Does being happy mean that we avoid conflict?</li>\r\n 	<li>How can we speak differently about spiritual practice and social justice so that we honor both where we are now and where we want to go?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nListen to the complete audio from the event below.\