f only two black women Zen “Senseis” or teachers,  she applies wisdom teaching to social issues and is a leading voice for Transformative Social Change.  In recognition of her work, angel Sensei received the first Enlightened Society Award from Sakyong Mipham Rinpoche.\r\n\r\nIf you enjoy Meditation in the City, throw us a buck or two. Any amount will help support this podcast. It’s easy, just click the link below!\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Pay Pal Podcast Donation\" href=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&amp;hosted_button_id=UXBZU59T4Z4D2\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://ny.shambhala.org/files/2011/08/paypal-donate-button-copy.png\" alt=\"paypal-donate-button copy\" width=\"214\" height=\"99\" /></a>\r\n\r\nPodcast production by <a title=\"Sonam Gray\" href=\"http://sonamgray.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sonamgray.com</a> and by David McKeel\r\n\r\nRead the article here: <a href=\"http://ny.shambhala.org/2015/01/02/buddhist-call-action-part-2-podcast-episode-no-61/\" target=\"_blank\">http://ny.shambhala.org/2015/01/02/buddhist-call-action-part-2-podcast-episode-no-61/</a>','A Buddhist Call to Action (part 2) – Podcast Episode No. 61','','inherit','closed','closed','','10602-revision-v1','','','2016-10-13 03:41:44','2016-10-13 03:41:44','',10602,'http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2016/10/13/10602-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10861,1,'2016-10-12 00:32:08','2016-10-12 00:32:08','<a class=\"entry-image-link\" href=\"http://localhost/akyodo/blog/2011/11/01/three-lessons-from-occupy/\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><img src=\"http://localhost/akyodo/wp-content/uploads/2007/10/FireAndTruth.png\" alt=\"FireAndTruth\" width=\"255\" height=\"170\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-111\" /></a>\r\n[audio mp3=\"http://angelkyodowilliams.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Buddhist_Call_to_Action_Part_Two.mp3\"][/audio]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"180\"]<a href=\"http://www.stitcher.com/s?fid=47138&amp;refid=stpr\"><img style=\"margin-top: 12%;\" src